# Kino EtherCAT

Welcome to the interactive documentation and testing suite for `kino_ethercat`.

## Testing & Diagnostics

The public `EtherCAT.state/0` lifecycle is:

`idle -> discovering -> awaiting_preop -> preop_ready -> operational`

with `activation_blocked` and `recovering` as the two non-happy-path runtime
states. `EtherCAT.await_running/1` waits for a usable session, while
`EtherCAT.await_operational/1` waits for cyclic OP.

### Start Here

* [Bring-up & Runtime Console](./testing/session_bringup.livemd)  
  Use this first for repeated manual testing on the loopback bench. It boots a
  fixed `:coupler`/`:inputs`/`:outputs` configuration and opens
  `KinoEtherCAT.diagnostics()` immediately.

### Scenario Notebooks

* [Loopback Smoke Test](./testing/loopback_smoke.livemd)  
  Fast digital I/O verification once the session is operational.
* [Distributed Clocks (DC) Lock](./testing/dc_lock.livemd)  
  Confirms DC lock and shows the final DC status snapshot.
* [Fault Tolerance (Manual)](./testing/fault_tolerance_manual.livemd)  
  Operator-guided disconnect/reconnect check for recovery behavior.
* [Watchdog Recovery](./testing/watchdog_recovery.livemd)  
  Stops domain cycling, observes watchdog fallback, then verifies recovery.
